      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<h3 id=\"TreasureEnvironment-TheEnvironment\">The Environment</h3><p>Thanks to the way the shot was laid out, I managed to accomplish a contained workflow to reach a nice look using a single column which I built procedurally in Houdini.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"column_v01_setup.png\" width=\"760\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/657424515/column_v01_setup.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762590629431&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=356\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/657424515/column_v01_setup.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762590629431&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"898\" data-width=\"1915\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"657621120\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"column_v01_setup.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"657424515\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"a4c80135-d3f5-4b1a-ae9d-3187a648244e\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/657424515/column_v01_setup.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762590629431&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1520&amp;height=712 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/657424515/column_v01_setup.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762590629431&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=356 1x\"></span><p>I approached the geometric proceduralism using voronoi fractures on the column, which combined with point wrangling, allowed me to wobble the edges, for a worn out marble column aesthetic.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"USD_exported_packed_instances.png\" width=\"760\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/657424515/USD_exported_packed_instances.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762590629481&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=345\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/657424515/USD_exported_packed_instances.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762590629481&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"871\" data-width=\"1916\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"657621127\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"USD_exported_packed_instances.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"657424515\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"616b89f1-b33e-4584-832c-9f8d1b2190eb\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/657424515/USD_exported_packed_instances.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762590629481&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1520&amp;height=690 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/657424515/USD_exported_packed_instances.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762590629481&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=345 1x\"></span><p>To keep the procedural wins going, I used RenderMan patterns to shade the columns. By using PxrRoundCube, I was able to achieve tileable texturing techniques in Katana, which was great because I was able to generate convincing textures without having to go to a painting application to generate new textures.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"marble_material_B_v01.png\" width=\"760\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/657424515/marble_material_B_v01.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762590629520&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=413\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/657424515/marble_material_B_v01.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762590629520&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"928\" data-width=\"1707\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"657621133\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"marble_material_B_v01.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"657424515\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"92f3824c-76f2-47b0-b765-88a855bbaf2f\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/657424515/marble_material_B_v01.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762590629520&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1520&amp;height=826 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/657424515/marble_material_B_v01.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762590629520&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=413 1x\"></span><p>A dragon’s lair has an epic story to tell, so conveying aging was crucial. Using PxrDirt was a really great way to communicate a worn out effect by adding additional grime and dust accumulation in the cracks. Leaving the pieces of column geometry separate also helped isolate this effect in a convincing way, which ultimately gave it a more natural look.</p><hr/>"
    }
